
## 4️⃣ Firewall

Layman meaning:
A firewall is a security guard for your network.

Simple example:

 It decides:

   Who can enter
   Who is blocked
   What is allowed

What firewall can monitor:

 Which websites are opened
 How long Facebook or WhatsApp is used
 Which applications are accessed
 What data/files are sent or received
 Incoming and outgoing traffic

IT meaning:

 Controls traffic using rules
 Protects from hackers
 Blocks unauthorized access